One of the "fun" things about Closure Compiler on Advanced Optimizations is managing externs when you can't compile the whole page in one package. A really easy way to make Browserify's output play nicer with Closure is to simply update the way it sets the require variable, from `require=` to `window["require"]=`. It's then possible (and easy) to write a library for compilation by Browserify/ClosureAO by simply using a string literal to set all names that should not be changed.

``` javascript
module.exports = {
    minifed:        internalFunc,
    "notMinified":  exportFunc
};
```

or

``` javascript
myClass.prototype.unassumingTask = unimportantStuffFunc;
myClass.prototype["doImportantStuff"] = importantStuffFunc;
```

